From 1959c4317a9b51a9ca6091eb622dab72dc13fd3a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 15:00:30 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase B fix: gh Contents API fallback when local git show
 fails
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Reported (still): warnings like "git show <sha>:<path> failed: path
exists on disk, but not in <sha>" for some files, and the affected
files render as fully-changed on the diff. Two prior attempts didn't
fix this:
  - Per-side fallback (patch 0072): gracefully handles the failure
    but the affected file shows as fully added on the head side.
  - merge-base instead of pr.base.sha (patch 0073): merge-base
    happens to equal pr.base.sha for some PRs (when the PR branch
    descends directly from the target tip without intermediate
    merges), so the SHA we ask `git show` doesn't change.

Even at the "right" SHA the file content lookup can fail when the
local clone's view of that SHA differs from GitHub's. The reasons
are usually clone-state related (partial fetch, force-pushed target
branch, etc.) but the symptom is the same: GitHub considers the file
modified, the local clone says it isn't there.

Fix: when `git show` fails, fall back to `gh api repos/{o}/{r}/
contents/{path}?ref={sha}` with `Accept: application/vnd.github.raw`.
GitHub's view of the SHA is authoritative for the PR's display, so
this is the right source of truth. Slow path (one API call per
failing file) only fires on `git show` failure — happy path stays
local.

If both fail (the file truly isn't in that ref per GitHub either)
the per-side resolver renders the affected side empty, which is the
correct visual ("added" if base is missing, "removed" if head is
missing).

- `IGhClient.apiRaw(path, accept)` — new method, returns response
  body as a string. Used so we can pass `application/vnd.github.raw`
  and get the file's raw bytes instead of a base64-wrapped JSON
  envelope.
- `IPullRequestProvider.getFileContent(owner, repo, ref, path)` —
  thin wrapper over the Contents API.
- `KrtGitContentProvider`: tries `gitService.showFile` first, falls
  back to `pullRequestProvider.getFileContent` on git failure, only
  returns null when both error.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
